{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848861916,"sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","part":{"id":"prt_d78d72c74001c1d2k5dRXmyEV7","messageID":"msg_d78d71860001j9UPX5GvAWZcHb","sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cfabdd623da74fb1b55bc8cf001c69dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Define `GarbageCollectorStats` struct for stats retrieval\n20:   - Fields: `Interval`, `OnceTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`\n21:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:129-133`\n22:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n23: \n24: - [x] **T1.2**: Define GC constants in `defaults.go`\n25:   - `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 * time.Minute`\n26:   - `GCBatchSize = 16`\n27:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:9` and `defaults.go:17`\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n29: \n30: ### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n31: \n32: - [x] **T2.1**: Define `GarbageCollector` struct with all required fields\n33:   - Fields: `manager`, `interval`, `onceTimeout`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `logger`, `idleTimeout`, `idleMu`\n34:   - Thread-safe: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout`\n35:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:11-20`\n36:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v`\n37: \n38: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n39:   - Apply defaults if `interval == 0`: use `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n40:   - Apply defaults if `onceTimeout == 0`: use `2 * time.Minute`\n41:   - Initialize `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n42:   - Create `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n43:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:22-38`\n44:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v && go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n45: \n46: ### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n47: \n48: - [x] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n49:   - Call `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n50:   - Launch `go gc.runLoop()`\n51:   - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n52:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:46-49`\n53:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n54: \n55: - [x] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n56:   - Call `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n57:   - Call `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n58:   - Returns only after goroutine exits\n59:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:51-54`\n60:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n61: \n62: - [x] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n63:   - Run in separate goroutine\n64:   - Execute `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n65:   - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n66:   - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n67:   - On `stopCh`: log `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and return\n68:   - On `ticker.C`: call `runOnce(context.Background())`\n69:   - Defer `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n70:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:56-73`\n71:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n72: \n73: ### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n74: \n75: - [x] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` with context timeout protection\n76:   - Create `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n77:   - Capture current time: `now := time.Now()`\n78:   - Get current `idleTimeout` via `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n79:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-80`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n81: \n82: - [x] **T4.2**: Implement expired sandbox query logic\n83:   - Call `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)`\n84:   - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list expired sandboxes\"`\n85:   - Return error if query fails\n86:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-86`\n87:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n88: \n89: - [x] **T4.3**: Implement inactive sandbox query logic\n90:   - Calculate `inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)`\n91:   - Call `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)`\n92:   - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\"`\n93:   - Return error if query fails\n94:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:88-93`\n95:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive -v`\n96: \n97: - [x] **T4.4**: Implement batch deletion loop\n98:   - Merge expired and inactive lists: `allSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)`\n99:   - For each sandbox, call `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)`\n100:   - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (continue)\n101:   - Handle other errors: log `\"gc delete failed\"` and continue\n102:   - Log successful deletion: `\"gc deleted sandbox\"` with reason\n103:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:95-108`\n104:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n105: \n106: - [x] **T4.5**: Implement batch size limit enforcement\n107:   - Verify at most `GCBatchSize` (16) items per category processed\n108:   - Ensure store size decreases appropriately after cleanup\n109:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-93` (limit param)\n110:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit -v`\n111: \n112: ### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n113: \n114: - [x] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n115:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n116:   - Update `gc.idleTimeout`\n117:   - Release mutex\n118:   - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n119:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:113-117`\n120:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n121: \n122: - [x] **T5.2**: Implement `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n123:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n124:   - Return current `gc.idleTimeout`\n125:   - Release mutex\n126:   - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n127:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:40-44`\n128:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n129: \n130: - [x] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n131:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n132:   - Return `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n133:   - Release mutex\n134:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:119-127`\n135:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n136: \n137: ### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n138: \n139: - [x] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe idleTimeout access\n140:   - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `GarbageCollector` struct\n141:   - Protect all reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n142:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:18-20`\n143:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n144: \n145: - [x] **T6.2**: Implement concurrent cleanup safety\n146:   - Multiple `runOnce()` calls can execute concurrently\n147:   - No race conditions on store operations\n148:   - No race conditions on idleTimeout reads\n149:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-111`\n150:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 7: Store Integration (ST-7)\n153: \n154: - [x] **T7.1**: Add `ListExpiredSandboxes` to Store interface\n155:   - Method signature: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n156:   - Query sandboxes where `ExpiresAt < before`\n157:   - Sort by `ExpiresAt` ascending (oldest first)\n158:   - Limit to `limit` items\n159:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:29` and `store.go:90-110`\n160:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListExpired -v`\n161: \n162: - [x] **T7.2**: Add `ListInactiveSandboxes` to Store interface\n163:   - Method signature: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n164:   - Query sandboxes where `LastActivity < before` (skip zero `LastActivity`)\n165:   - Sort by `LastActivity` ascending (most inactive first)\n166:   - Limit to `limit` items\n167:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:30` and `store.go:112-132`\n168:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListInactive -v`\n169: \n170: - [x] **T7.3**: Implement MemoryStore GC query methods\n171:   - Use `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe reads\n172:   - Implement sorting for deterministic cleanup order\n173:   - Implement limit truncation for batch size enforcement\n174:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go:90-132`\n175:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -v`\n176: \n177: ### Phase 8: Deletion Reason Classification (ST-8)\n178: \n179: - [x] **T8.1**: Implement `determineDeletionReason` helper function\n180:   - If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n181:   - If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n182:   - Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n183:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go:167-175`\n184:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDetermineDeletionReason -v`\n185: \n186: ### Phase 9: Integration & Validation (ST-9)\n187: \n188: - [x] **T9.1**: Integrate GC with SandboxLifecycleManager\n189:   - GC delegates deletion to `manager.DeleteSandbox`\n190:   - Manager handles K8s resource deletion + store cleanup\n191:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:98`\n192:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n193: \n194: - [x] **T9.2**: Verify error handling flow\n195:   - NotFound errors silently ignored\n196:   - List errors abort cycle but don't crash GC\n197:   - Delete errors logged but continue processing\n198:   - GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n199:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-108`\n200:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n201: \n202: - [x] **T9.3**: All unit tests pass\n203:   - `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n204:   - Coverage: >80% for garbage_collector.go\n205:   - No race conditions\n206:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Task Dependencies\n211: \n212: ```\n213: T1.1 → T1.2\n214:   ↓\n215: T2.1 → T2.2\n216:   ↓\n217: T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3\n218:   ↓\n219: T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5\n220:   ↓\n221: T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n222:   ↓\n223: T6.1 → T6.2\n224:   ↓\n225: T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3\n226:   ↓\n227: T8.1\n228:   ↓\n229: T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## Verification Commands\n235: \n236: | Task | Verification Command |\n237: |------|----------------------|\n238: | All GC tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v` |\n239: | Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v` |\n240: | Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v` |\n241: | Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce -v` |\n242: | Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v` |\n243: | Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep garbage_collector` |\n244: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n245: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Acceptance Criteria\n250: \n251: - [x] GarbageCollector runs as background goroutine with ticker loop\n252: - [x] Immediate cleanup on start, then periodic cleanup every `interval`\n253: - [x] Graceful shutdown via `Stop()` with `WaitGroup` synchronization\n254: - [x] Expired sandbox cleanup based on `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n255: - [x] Inactive sandbox cleanup based on `LastActivity` + `idleTimeout`\n256: - [x] Batch size limit: max 16 items per category per cycle\n257: - [x] NotFound errors silently ignored (already deleted)\n258: - [x] Other errors logged but don't stop cleanup cycle\n259: - [x] Thread-safe `idleTimeout` runtime configuration via `SetIdleTimeout`\n260: - [x] Stats retrieval via `GetStats()` for monitoring\n261: - [x] Store methods: `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n262: - [x] Deletion reason classification: `MaxDurationReached`, `IdleTimeout`, `UserRequest`\n263: - [x] All unit tests pass (9 tests)\n264: - [x] No race conditions detected\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Files Modified/Created\n269: \n270: | File | Status | Description |\n271: |------|--------|-------------|\n272: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ✓ Complete | GarbageCollector implementation (133 lines) |\n273: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | ✓ Complete | Comprehensive test suite (9 tests, 379 lines) |\n274: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ✓ Complete | Added ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes |\n275: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GC methods to Store interface |\n276: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | ✓ Complete | Added determineDeletionReason helper |\n277: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GarbageCollectorInterval constant |\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Notes\n282: \n283: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n284: - **Implementation 100% complete**\n285: - **All 9 tests pass with full coverage**\n286: - **Thread-safe implementation**: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout` for concurrent access\n287: - **Graceful degradation**: GC continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n288: - **Batch processing**: Limit of 16 items per category prevents resource exhaustion\n289: - **Context timeout protection**: Single GC cycle limited to `onceTimeout` (default 2 minutes)\n290: - **Integration**: GC delegates deletion to `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## Implementation Timeline\n295: \n296: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n297: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n298: | Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n299: | Phase 2: Struct & Constructor | T2.1, T2.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n300: | Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n301: | Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic | T4.1-T4.5 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n302: | Phase 5: Runtime Config | T5.1-T5.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n303: | Phase 6: Concurrent Safety | T6.1, T6.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n304: | Phase 7: Store Integration | T7.1-T7.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n305: | Phase 8: Deletion Reason | T8.1 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n306: | Phase 9: Integration & Validation | T9.1-T9.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n307: \n308: **Total Progress: 100% Complete (24/24 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 308 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define `GarbageCollectorStats` struct for stats retrieval\n  - Fields: `Interval`, `OnceTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848861890,"end":1775848861914}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848861920,"sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","part":{"id":"prt_d78d730a6001g50QDZ9kICe1MV","messageID":"msg_d78d71860001j9UPX5GvAWZcHb","sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-55352afe24d14be791efeb7dd9e357ae","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: GarbageCollector struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `GarbageCollector` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `manager *SandboxLifecycleManager` for sandbox deletion delegation\n26:   - `interval time.Duration` for GC cycle interval\n27:   - `onceTimeout time.Duration` for single GC cycle timeout\n28:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for graceful shutdown signal\n29:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n30:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n31:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` for idle sandbox cleanup threshold\n32:   - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` for idleTimeout concurrent access protection\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector constructor\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n36: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, interval, onceTimeout, logger)`\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n38:   - `interval` defaulted to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes) if zero\n39:   - `onceTimeout` defaulted to `2 * time.Minute` if zero\n40:   - `idleTimeout` initialized from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n41:   - `stopCh` initialized as `make(chan struct{})`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector with custom interval\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n45: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 5*time.Minute, 3*time.Minute, logger)`\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n47:   - `interval` = `5 * time.Minute`\n48:   - `onceTimeout` = `3 * time.Minute`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector lifecycle\n53: \n54: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods for the GC background goroutine.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Start launches runLoop\n57: - **GIVEN** a `GarbageCollector` instance\n58: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Start()`\n59: - **THEN** `gc.wg.Add(1)` SHALL be called\n60: - AND `gc.runLoop()` SHALL be launched as a goroutine\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Stop signals shutdown\n63: - **GIVEN** a running `GarbageCollector`\n64: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Stop()`\n65: - **THEN** `close(gc.stopCh)` SHALL be called\n66: - AND `gc.wg.Wait()` SHALL block until goroutine completes\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: runLoop initial execution\n69: - **GIVEN** a started `GarbageCollector`\n70: - **WHEN** `runLoop` begins\n71: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called immediately\n72: - AND ticker SHALL be created with `time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: runLoop ticker-driven execution\n75: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n76: - **WHEN** ticker fires\n77: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: runLoop stops on stopCh\n80: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n81: - **WHEN** `stopCh` receives signal\n82: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")` SHALL be called\n83: - AND goroutine SHALL return\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Requirement: runOnce GC cycle\n88: \n89: The system SHALL implement `runOnce` for a single garbage collection cycle.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: runOnce with context timeout\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n93: - **WHEN** calling `runOnce(ctx)`\n94: - **THEN** `context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)` SHALL be created\n95: - AND cancel SHALL be deferred\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: runOnce queries expired sandboxes\n98: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n99: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n100: - **THEN** `gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n101: - AND result SHALL be limited to `GCBatchSize=16`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: runOnce queries inactive sandboxes\n104: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n105: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n106: - **THEN** `inactiveBefore = now.Add(-idleTimeout)` SHALL be computed\n107: - AND `gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandbox\n110: - **GIVEN** an expired sandbox with `ExpiresAt < now`\n111: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n112: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n113: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandbox\n116: - **GIVEN** an inactive sandbox with `LastActivity < inactiveBefore`\n117: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n118: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n119: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: runOnce ignores NotFound error\n122: - **GIVEN** a sandbox that no longer exists\n123: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n124: - **THEN** error SHALL be ignored with `continue`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion success\n127: - **GIVEN** a successfully deleted sandbox\n128: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n129: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)` SHALL be called\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion failure\n132: - **GIVEN** a deletion that fails (not NotFound)\n133: - **WHEN** error occurs\n134: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n135: - AND processing SHALL continue for remaining sandboxes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Batch size limitation\n140: \n141: The system SHALL limit cleanup operations per cycle to prevent cluster overload.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: GCBatchSize constant\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n145: - **WHEN** reading constants\n146: - **THEN** `GCBatchSize` SHALL be `16`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit\n149: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListExpiredSandboxes`\n150: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n151: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n152: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit\n155: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListInactiveSandboxes`\n156: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n157: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n158: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Combined batch limit\n161: - **GIVEN** 20 expired and 20 inactive sandboxes\n162: - **WHEN** `runOnce` executes\n163: - **THEN** at most `16 + 16 = 32` sandboxes SHALL be processed\n164: - AND remaining sandboxes SHALL be processed in subsequent cycles\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Store interface extensions\n169: \n170: The system SHALL extend the Store interface with GC-specific query methods.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Store interface includes GC methods\n173: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n174: - **WHEN** reading the `Store` interface\n175: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n176:   - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n177:   - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n180: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n181: - **WHEN** calling `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n182: - **THEN** all sandboxes with `ExpiresAt.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n183: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n184: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n187: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n188: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n189: - **THEN** all sandboxes with non-zero `LastActivity` and `LastActivity.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n190: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n191: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes skips zero LastActivity\n194: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `LastActivity.IsZero() == true`\n195: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n196: - **THEN** that sandbox SHALL NOT be included in results\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: Runtime configuration\n201: \n202: The system SHALL support runtime configuration of GC parameters.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout method\n205: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n206: - **WHEN** calling `gc.SetIdleTimeout(30 * time.Minute)`\n207: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.Lock()` SHALL be acquired\n208: - AND `gc.idleTimeout` SHALL be updated to `30 * time.Minute`\n209: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: getIdleTimeout method\n212: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n213: - **WHEN** calling `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n214: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.RLock()` SHALL be acquired\n215: - AND current `idleTimeout` value SHALL be returned\n216: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: GetStats method\n219: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n220: - **WHEN** calling `gc.GetStats()`\n221: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorStats` SHALL be returned with:\n222:   - `Interval`: current GC cycle interval\n223:   - `OnceTimeout`: current single-cycle timeout\n224:   - `IdleTimeout`: current idle threshold\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorStats struct\n227: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n228: - **WHEN** reading `GarbageCollectorStats`\n229: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n230:   - `Interval time.Duration`\n231:   - `OnceTimeout time.Duration`\n232:   - `IdleTimeout time.Duration`\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: Deletion reason determination\n237: \n238: The system SHALL categorize deletion reasons for logging and tracking.\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason function\n241: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n242: - **WHEN** calling `determineDeletionReason(sandbox, now, idleTimeout)`\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL return `DeletionReason`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: MaxDurationReached reason\n246: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`\n247: - **WHEN** determining reason\n248: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be returned\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: IdleTimeout reason\n251: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with non-zero `LastActivity` and `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`\n252: - **WHEN** determining reason and `ExpiresAt` not yet reached\n253: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be returned\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: UserRequest fallback reason\n256: - **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n257: - **WHEN** determining reason\n258: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be returned as fallback\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ### Requirement: DeletionReason constants\n263: \n264: The system SHALL define deletion reason constants for categorization.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonIdleTimeout constant\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading constants\n269: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached constant\n272: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n273: - **WHEN** reading constants\n274: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be `\"MaxDurationReached\"`\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonUserRequest constant\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n278: - **WHEN** reading constants\n279: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be `\"UserRequest\"`\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Default constants\n284: \n285: The system SHALL define default timeout constants.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorInterval constant\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n289: - **WHEN** reading constants\n290: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constant\n293: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n294: - **WHEN** reading constants\n295: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxTTL constant\n298: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n299: - **WHEN** reading constants\n300: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: Concurrent safety\n305: \n306: The system SHALL handle concurrent access safely.\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: idleMu protects idleTimeout\n309: - **GIVEN** `GarbageCollector` with `idleMu sync.RWMutex`\n310: - **WHEN** concurrent reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n311: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n312: - AND `RLock` SHALL be used for reads\n313: - AND `Lock` SHALL be used for writes\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Store mutex protection\n316: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with `sync.RWMutex`\n317: - **WHEN** concurrent `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n318: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: runOnce called from single goroutine\n321: - **GIVEN** `runLoop` design\n322: - **WHEN** GC is running\n323: - **THEN** `runOnce` SHALL only be called from the single `runLoop` goroutine\n324: - AND no concurrent `runOnce` calls SHALL occur from GC itself\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ### Requirement: Deletion delegation\n329: \n330: The system SHALL delegate actual deletion to SandboxLifecycleManager.\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox delegation\n333: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` processing a sandbox\n334: - **WHEN** calling deletion\n335: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n336: - AND deletion SHALL handle both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles K8s resources\n339: - **GIVEN** `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n340: - **WHEN** deletion executes\n341: - **THEN** `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes) SHALL be deleted\n342: - AND `SandboxClaimGVR` SHALL be deleted if `Kind == SandboxClaimKind`\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ### Requirement: Integration with HTTPServer\n347: \n348: The system SHALL integrate GC with the HTTPServer lifecycle.\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: GC created in HTTPServer\n351: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n352: - **WHEN** HTTPServer is initialized\n353: - **THEN** `NewGarbageCollector` SHALL be called with:\n354:   - `manager` = `SandboxLifecycleManager`\n355:   - `interval` = `config.GCInterval`\n356:   - `onceTimeout` = `config.GCOnceTimeout`\n357:   - `logger` = server logger\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: GC started on server start\n360: - **GIVEN** HTTPServer with GC\n361: - **WHEN** server starts\n362: - **THEN** `gc.Start()` SHALL be called\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: GC stopped on server shutdown\n365: - **GIVEN** running HTTPServer with GC\n366: - **WHEN** server shuts down\n367: - **THEN** `gc.Stop()` SHALL be called\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Unit tests for GarbageCollector\n372: \n373: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for GC behavior.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n377: - **WHEN** running tests\n378: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n379:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n380:   - Custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval\n383: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n384: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 0, 0, logger)`\n385: - **THEN** default values SHALL be applied:\n386:   - `interval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n387:   - `onceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_StartStop\n390: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n391: - **WHEN** running tests\n392: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n393:   - `Start()` launches goroutine\n394:   - `Stop()` completes without hanging\n395:   - Goroutine exits cleanly\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired\n398: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n399: - **WHEN** running tests with expired sandbox\n400: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n401:   - Expired sandbox is deleted\n402:   - Active sandbox remains\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n406: - **WHEN** running tests with inactive sandbox\n407: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n408:   - Inactive sandbox (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is deleted\n409:   - Active sandbox remains\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n413: - **WHEN** running tests with 20 expired sandboxes\n414: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n415:   - At most `GCBatchSize=16` sandboxes are deleted per cycle\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError\n418: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n419: - **WHEN** running tests\n420: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n421:   - All sandboxes are processed even if some deletions fail\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_GetStats\n424: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n425: - **WHEN** running tests\n426: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n427:   - `GetStats()` returns correct interval, timeout, idleTimeout\n428:   - `SetIdleTimeout()` updates stats correctly\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce\n431: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n432: - **WHEN** running tests with concurrent `runOnce` calls\n433: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n434:   - Store handles concurrent access safely\n435:   - No race conditions occur\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ### Requirement: Integration tests for GC\n440: \n441: The system SHALL have integration tests verifying GC with lifecycle manager.\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: Full GC flow test\n444: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n445: - **WHEN** running tests\n446: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n447:   - GC deletes expired sandboxes\n448:   - Store is updated after deletion\n449:   - Multiple GC cycles process remaining sandboxes\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ### Requirement: Error handling\n454: \n455: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in GC operations.\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes error\n458: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n459: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` returns error\n460: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n461: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes error\n464: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n465: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` returns error\n466: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n467: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox NotFound handling\n470: - **GIVEN** a sandbox already deleted\n471: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n472: - **THEN** error SHALL be silently ignored\n473: - AND GC SHALL continue to next sandbox\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ### Requirement: File structure\n478: \n479: The system SHALL organize GC files correctly.\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: garbage_collector.go location\n482: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n483: - **WHEN** listing files\n484: - **THEN** `garbage_collector.go` SHALL exist with:\n485:   - `GarbageCollector` struct\n486:   - `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n487:   - `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce` methods\n488:   - `SetIdleTimeout`, `getIdleTimeout`, `GetStats` methods\n489:   - `GCBatchSize` constant\n490:   - `GarbageCollectorStats` struct\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: garbage_collector_test.go location\n493: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n494: - **WHEN** listing files\n495: - **THEN** `garbage_collector_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: store.go with GC methods\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n499: - **WHEN** reading file\n500: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be implemented\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: types.go with Store interface\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading `Store` interface\n505: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be declared\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: LifecycleConfig integration\n510: \n511: The system SHALL use LifecycleConfig for GC configuration.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: LifecycleConfig GC fields\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n515: - **WHEN** reading `LifecycleConfig`\n516: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n517:   - `GCInterval time.Duration`\n518:   - `GCOnceTimeout time.Duration`\n519:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration`\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig GC defaults\n522: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n523: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultLifecycleConfig()`\n524: - **THEN** returned config SHALL have:\n525:   - `GCInterval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes)\n526:   - `GCOnceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n527:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout` = `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## Implementation Files\n532: \n533: | File | Purpose |\n534: |------|---------|\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector implementation with Start/Stop/runOnce |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes implementations |\n538: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Store interface extensions, DeletionReason constants |\n539: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | determineDeletionReason, LifecycleConfig GC fields |\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | GarbageCollectorInterval, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constants |\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## Dependencies\n545: \n546: | Package | Purpose |\n547: |---------|---------|\n548: | `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles |\n549: | `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency |\n550: | `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n551: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo struct |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | DeleteOptions |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## GC Flow Diagram\n558: \n559: ```\n560: GarbageCollector\n561: │\n562: ├── Start()\n563: │   └── wg.Add(1)\n564: │   └── go runLoop()\n565: │       ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n566: │       ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n567: │       ├── select { stopCh, ticker.C }\n568: │       │   ├── ticker.C → runOnce(ctx)\n569: │       │   └── stopCh → return\n570: │       └── wg.Done()\n571: │\n572: ├── Stop()\n573: │   ├── close(stopCh)\n574: │   └── wg.Wait()\n575: │\n576: └── runOnce(ctx)\n577:     ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n578:     ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n579:     ├── inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n580:     ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n581:     ├── for sb in expired + inactive:\n582:     │   ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n583:     │   ├── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n584:     │   └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n585:     └── return nil\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ## Configuration Values\n591: \n592: | Parameter | Default | Configurable | Source |\n593: |-----------|---------|--------------|--------|\n594: | `interval` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n595: | `onceTimeout` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n596: | `idleTimeout` | 15m | Yes (runtime) | `SetIdleTimeout` |\n597: | `batchSize` | 16 | No (const) | `GCBatchSize` |\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## Deletion Reasons\n602: \n603: | Reason | Condition | Description |\n604: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n605: | `IdleTimeout` | `LastActivity + idleTimeout < now` AND `ExpiresAt > now` | Sandbox inactive for too long |\n606: | `MaxDurationReached` | `ExpiresAt < now` | Sandbox exceeded maximum TTL |\n607: | `UserRequest` | Neither above | Fallback for manual deletion |\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Validation Checklist\n612: \n613: - [ ] GarbageCollector struct defined with all required fields\n614: - [ ] NewGarbageCollector constructor with default fallbacks\n615: - [ ] Start() launches background goroutine\n616: - [ ] Stop() signals shutdown and waits for completion\n617: - [ ] runLoop uses ticker for periodic execution\n618: - [ ] runOnce has context timeout protection\n619: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expired by ExpiresAt\n620: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries inactive by LastActivity\n621: - [ ] Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) enforced per query\n622: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n623: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n624: - [ ] determineDeletionReason categorizes deletions correctly\n625: - [ ] SetIdleTimeout runtime configuration supported\n626: - [ ] GetStats returns current configuration\n627: - [ ] idleMu protects concurrent idleTimeout access\n628: - [ ] Store interface includes GC query methods\n629: - [ ] MemoryStore implements GC query methods\n630: - [ ] LifecycleConfig includes GC parameters\n631: - [ ] DefaultLifecycleConfig provides GC defaults\n632: - [ ] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n633: - [ ] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n634: - [ ] Integration tests verify full GC flow\n635: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n636: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n637: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 637 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848861894,"end":1775848861917}}}}
