{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848895023,"sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","part":{"id":"prt_d78d786a4001M4H6cO4LNUFhy0","messageID":"msg_d78d74ffe001PPeOPtwxUABOlk","sessionID":"ses_28729480cffecjf20CiBHcHbQX","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n### Completed (100% - 24/24 tasks)\n\n**Core Implementation:**\n- GarbageCollector struct with 8 required fields (manager, interval, onceTimeout, stopCh, wg, logger, idleTimeout, idleMu)\n- NewGarbageCollector constructor with default fallbacks (interval: 2m, onceTimeout: 2m, idleTimeout: from config)\n- Start/Stop lifecycle management with WaitGroup synchronization\n- Background ticker loop (runLoop) with immediate execution + periodic cleanup\n- runOnce implementation with context timeout protection (onceTimeout)\n- Expired sandbox cleanup based on `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n- Inactive sandbox cleanup based on `LastActivity + idleTimeout`\n- Batch size limit: max 16 items per category per cycle (GCBatchSize=16)\n- NotFound errors silently ignored, other errors logged but continue\n- Thread-safe `idleTimeout` configuration via `idleMu sync.RWMutex`\n- Runtime configuration via SetIdleTimeout/GetStats methods\n- Deletion reason classification: MaxDurationReached, IdleTimeout, UserRequest\n\n**Store Extensions:**\n- ListExpiredSandboxes method (sorted by ExpiresAt ascending)\n- ListInactiveSandboxes method (sorted by LastActivity ascending)\n- Both methods enforce limit parameter for batch control\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- 9 unit tests covering: constructor, lifecycle, expired/inactive cleanup, batch limit, error handling, stats, concurrent safety\n- All tests pass with >80% coverage for garbage_collector.go\n- No race conditions detected\n\n**Files Modified:** garbage_collector.go (133 lines), garbage_collector_test.go (379 lines), store.go, types.go, lifecycle.go, defaults.go\n\n### Deferred\n\n**Future Enhancements (Open Questions):**\n1. **Prometheus metrics export** - Currently uses structured logging only; metric